WEBVTT

00:00.050 --> 00:02.800
Let's work on forming the /ʃ/ sound.

00:03.750 --> 00:07.300
Let your jaw release slightly so your lips are parted.

00:08.050 --> 00:11.000
Bring the blade of your tongue up to the roof of your mouth...

00:11.650 --> 00:15.250
...and push the air out around the sides of the tongue.

00:16.250 --> 00:18.550
Let your hand touch your throat,...

00:19.100 --> 00:21.450
...make sure you don't feel any vibration.

00:23.850 --> 00:28.850
/ʃ/, /ʃ/, /ʃ/.

00:30.100 --> 00:33.500
Here's /ʃ/ in the beginning of some words.

00:34.400 --> 00:39.000
Ship, Shape, Shower.

00:41.050 --> 00:42.700
Here it is in the middle.

00:43.800 --> 00:48.500
Pushing, Fishing, Smashes.

00:49.800 --> 00:53.800
And here is /ʃ/ at the end of some words.

00:54.800 --> 00:59.900
Bash, Fish, Dish.

01:02.550 --> 01:07.250
Listen to these pairs of words to hear the contrasting sounds.

01:08.350 --> 01:11.250
Ship, Chip.

01:12.950 --> 01:15.900
Ship, Sip.

01:17.800 --> 01:21.000
Cash, Catch.

01:22.500 --> 01:25.650
Mash, Mass.

01:27.500 --> 01:31.750
And here are some sentences that use the /ʃ/ sound.

01:34.500 --> 01:38.400
The fish dish on the ship was smashing!

01:40.300 --> 01:43.100
She paid cash for the shower cap.

01:45.500 --> 01:49.550
/ʃ/, /ʃ/, /ʃ/.

01:50.750 --> 01:51.700
Great job!

